<h1>IMC Seminar</h1> 

This seminar is open to all
Warwick's undergraduates. Its
objective is to select and prepare Warwick's team for the
<a href="http://www.imc-math.org.uk/">22d International Mathematical Competition (IMC)</a> 
that will take place 27 July - 2 August 2015 in Bulgaria.<p>

Those students who would like to be considered for the team (MMath and MSc students are also eligible) should take
two selection tests: 
<b>1-4pm on 18 February in B3.02</b> and 
<b>1-4pm on 4 March in B3.03</b>. 

We will also have training sessions
<b>1-2pm</b> on the following Wednesdays: <b>14, 21, 28 January; 4, 11, 25 February, and 11 March
(all in B3.03)</b>, open to everyone interested in problem-solving.<p>



No prior registration is required and you do not need to be a math 
major in order to attend.
No credit will be awarded for taking the seminar.<p>

Further information will be added here in due time. 
As an extra preparation for the seminar, we recommend solving past problems (available online 
with solutions) from the following
competitions:
 <lu>
 <li>  
<a href="http://www.imc-math.org.uk/">International Mathematical Competition (IMC)</a></li> 
<li><a href="http://amc.maa.org/a-activities/a7-problems/putnamindex.shtml">Putnam
Competition</a></li>
<li><a href="http://vjimc.osu.cz/history">Vojtech Jarnik Mathematical Competition</a>
</li>
 </lu><p>


Good luck!<br>
<a href="http://homepages.warwick.ac.uk/~maskat/">Oleg Pikhurko</a><br>
